{"name":"Perfect Mimicry","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\" data-sheets-value=\"{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Trigger: a humanoid hostile creature just used a single action activity\\n\\nYour able to mimic an action you only just saw with near perfect accuracy. Make a society check. The GM sets the DC based on the circumstances&mdash;it&rsquo;s generally at least a hard DC of the creature&rsquo;s level. If you already possess the ability to make the same action, treat your result as 1 level higher.\\n\\nSuccess: You perform the same action the creature took.\\nCritical Failure: You trip over yourself attempting the maneuver. You fall Prone.\\n\\nThis effect cannot be used to copy actions that require components or objects that you do not possess. For instance, you could copy a spell with somatic and verbal components, but not one with material components unless you also had the components. You can replace objects where it makes sense. For instance, if a creature uses a unique attack utilizing a maul, you could perform the same attack with any 2-handed weapon. The GM will determine which effects ultimately can be copied.\\n&quot;}\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{&quot;2&quot;:33555329,&quot;3&quot;:{&quot;1&quot;:0},&quot;10&quot;:0,&quot;11&quot;:4,&quot;12&quot;:0,&quot;28&quot;:1}\">Trigger: a humanoid hostile creature just used a single action activity<br /><br />Your able to mimic an action you only just saw with near perfect accuracy. Make a society check. The GM sets the DC based on the circumstances&mdash;it&rsquo;s generally at least a hard DC of the creature&rsquo;s level. If you already possess the ability to make the same action, treat your result as 1 level higher.<br /><br />Success: You perform the same action the creature took.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\" data-sheets-value=\"{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Trigger: a humanoid hostile creature just used a single action activity\\n\\nYour able to mimic an action you only just saw with near perfect accuracy. Make a society check. The GM sets the DC based on the circumstances&mdash;it&rsquo;s generally at least a hard DC of the creature&rsquo;s level. If you already possess the ability to make the same action, treat your result as 1 level higher.\\n\\nSuccess: You perform the same action the creature took.\\nCritical Failure: You trip over yourself attempting the maneuver. You fall Prone.\\n\\nThis effect cannot be used to copy actions that require components or objects that you do not possess. For instance, you could copy a spell with somatic and verbal components, but not one with material components unless you also had the components. You can replace objects where it makes sense. For instance, if a creature uses a unique attack utilizing a maul, you could perform the same attack with any 2-handed weapon. The GM will determine which effects ultimately can be copied.\\n&quot;}\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{&quot;2&quot;:33555329,&quot;3&quot;:{&quot;1&quot;:0},&quot;10&quot;:0,&quot;11&quot;:4,&quot;12&quot;:0,&quot;28&quot;:1}\"><br />Critical Failure: You trip over yourself attempting the maneuver. You fall Prone.<br /><br />This effect cannot be used to copy actions that require components or objects that you do not possess. For instance, you could copy a spell with somatic and verbal components, but not one with material components unless you also had the components. You can replace objects where it makes sense. For instance, if a creature uses a unique attack utilizing a maul, you could perform the same attack with any 2-handed weapon. The GM will determine which effects ultimately can be copied.<br /></span></p>"},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":["general","skill"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.713,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":15},"fea