{"name":"Smells like magic","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\" data-sheets-value=\"{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;You have trained your senses to such a degree that you can smell magic in the air. You gain imprecise scent with a range of 30 feet. This means you can use your sense of smell to determine a creature&rsquo;s location. The GM will usually double the range if you&rsquo;re downwind from the creature or halve the range if you&rsquo;re upwind. This effect only applies to creature's currently affected by a magical effect. If you have an imprecise scent from another feature or effect, then you instead gain a +2 status bonus to detecting creatures affected by magic.\\r\\n&quot;}\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{&quot;2&quot;:33555329,&quot;3&quot;:{&quot;1&quot;:0},&quot;10&quot;:0,&quot;11&quot;:4,&quot;12&quot;:0,&quot;28&quot;:1}\">You have trained your senses to such a degree that you can smell magic in the air. You gain imprecise scent with a range of 30 feet. This means you can use your sense of smell to determine a creature&rsquo;s location. The GM will usually double the range if you&rsquo;re downwind from the creature or halve the range if you&rsquo;re upwind. This effect only applies to creature's currently affected by a magical effect. If you have an imprecise scent from another feature or effect, then you instead gain a +2 status bonus to detecting creatures affected by magic.<br /></span></p>"},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":["general","skill"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.713,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":2},"featType":{"value":"skill"},"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ajNtWZ644V4dHnNv":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.surles-feats.QYzkrKyytGGoxbE7"}},"_id":"m4W7hR2Gq0Sdw8Aa"}
{"name":"Survival Instincts","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\" data-sheets-value=\"{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Requirements: An unobserved, undetected, or hidden creature makes an attack roll against you, or causes you to make a saving throw.\\r\\nYou sharpened instincts alert you to danger. Gain a +1 circumstance bonus to your AC or, if the trigger was due to a saving throw, a +1 circumstance bonus to the saving throw. If triggering creature critically fails its action against you, you gain an additional reaction. If you have legendary proficiency in survival, then you gain the additional reaction on a failure as well.&quot;}\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{&quot;2&quot;:33555329,&quot;3&quot;:{&quot;1&quot;:0},&quot;10&quot;:0,&quot;11&quot;:4,&quot;12&quot;:0,&quot;28&quot;:1}\">Requirements: An unobserved, undetected, or hidden creature makes an attack roll against you, or causes you to make a saving throw.<br />You sharpened instincts alert you to danger. Gain a +1 circumstance bonus to your AC or, if the trigger was due to a saving throw, a +1 circumstance bonus to the saving throw. If triggering creature critically fails its action against you, you gain an additional reaction. If you have legendary proficiency in survival, then you gain the additional reaction on a failure as well.</span></p>"},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":["general","skill"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.713,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":7},"featType":{"value":"skill"},"actionType":{"value":"reaction"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ajNtWZ644V4dHnNv":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.surles-feats.Rr4ftzLvzABDmXuA"}},"_id":"UB2dcBMHBrVW7jSA"}
